1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:03,507
The syntax is the set's of formulas themselves,

2
00:00:03,607 --> 00:00:05,837
and they are governed by a formal calculus

3
00:00:06,066 --> 00:00:08,735
The semantics is the interpretation of these symbols.

4
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:11,732
Truth in the syntactical side is given by a valid

5
00:00:11,832 --> 00:00:15,322
proof in a deductive calculus. Here Sigma proves phi means

6
00:00:15,422 --> 00:00:18,168
that there is a proof of phi using the logical

7
00:00:18,268 --> 00:00:21,944
axioms and premises in Sigma following the rules of inference

8
00:00:22,066 --> 00:00:25,362
This is a mechanical process which can be visualized as a tree

9
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:28,346
Truth in the semantical side is based on Tarki's definition of

10
00:00:28,446 --> 00:00:30,999
truth. Namely that something is true iff it is true in

11
00:00:31,099 --> 00:00:34,094
all models. Here Sigma models phi means that in every structure

12
00:00:34,194 --> 00:00:37,190
where Sigma is satisfied -- i.e. each sentence in Sigma happens

13
00:00:37,290 --> 00:00:38,909
to be true-- phi is also satisfied.

14
00:00:39,066 --> 00:00:42,274
For example, if we have an order relation in our vocabulary and

15
00:00:42,374 --> 00:00:45,793
Sigma is the set of sentences expressing that the order relation is

16
00:00:45,893 --> 00:00:49,573
transitive and irreflexive, then we can show that it is also assymetric.

17
00:00:49,673 --> 00:00:53,302
So, any structure satisfying each of the two conditions in Sigma, which

18
00:00:53,402 --> 00:00:57,083
happens in any irreflexive partially ordered set, such as a number line,

19
00:00:57,183 --> 00:00:59,551
or a tree, or a lattice, will also satisfy phi.

20
00:00:59,666 --> 00:01:03,036
Another way to see this, is that there is no structure in the

21
00:01:03,136 --> 00:01:07,472
mathematical universe, which makes Sigma true but which makes phi false. It is

22
00:01:07,572 --> 00:01:11,112
natural to wonder what is the relation between these two worlds.

23
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:15,818
In 1929, Godel proved that these two relations are equivalent

24
00:01:15,918 --> 00:01:19,170
for First order logic. To understand this, we will have

25
00:01:19,270 --> 00:01:21,974
to dive into the basics of mathematical logic.

